Second, find out how many warriors you have, and try to get one of them in each group. Once you have one cleric and one warrior in each group(if this is possible) then fill in the rest with others. I usually will team the highest lvl enchanter/main mezzer for the raid with the second group that is not the pull team, merely for the fact that group 1's cleric will be healing the puller and main tank most often. Any group that doesnt have at least one cleric, I always try and get 2 other healer types in there if I can. Shamans as main healer of a group on a raid is a bad idea, since they will be asked for buffs constantly throughout. Once you get your groups balanced somewhat, the rest is much easier. You can do all the standard things raid leaders do to prepare, I.E. get maps, research drops, etc. But if you dont balance groups or get them going quick enough on pick up raids, it gets difficult to keep people patient sometimes. <br>
